<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870702-0172 </DOCNO><HL> UST Unit to Sell Some Brands</HL><DD> 07/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> UST AZEATENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> GREENWICH, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   U.S. Tobacco Co., a subsidiary of UST Inc., said it agreed to sell almost all of its dry snuff brands, which represent less than 3% of its total smokeless tobacco sales, to Helme Tobacco Co., a subsidiary of American Maize-Products Co., for $36.5 million.    The brands being sold include Bruton, C.C. Devoe, Red Rose and Red Rooster. U.S. Tobacco said the sale is subject to government antitrust clearance.    American Maize, Stamford, Conn., is a diversified food and tobacco concern. </TEXT></DOC>